
1. grep: Pattern Searching

Searching for a Specific Pattern:
grep "Linux" example.txt

Case-Insensitive Search:
grep -i "linux" example.txt


Displaying Line Numbers:
grep -n "grep" example.txt


Inverse Search:
To display lines that do not match a specific pattern, use the “-v” option
grep -v "example" example.txt
The output will display all lines that do not contain the word “example”:
